== East German Cup (1949-1991) ==

[[East Germany]] also had its own national cup: the [[FDGB Cup|FDGB Pokal]], the cup of the  ''Freie Deutsche Gewerkschaftsbund'', the association of the East German trade unions. It   was introduced in 1949 and awarded annually until 1991 after [[German reunification]] in 1990 led to the merger of the football leagues of the two Germanys.

== Women's German Cup ==

Since 1981 women's football clubs have competed for the [[Women's German Cup]] (Frauen-DFB-Pokal).
